zaXXon: :) Thanks Joan 
Hello everybody, welcome
For those of you who are joining me for the first time - my name is Zahari, or just Harry :) and I'll be glad to spend a 
few hours with you, talking about our favorite game.
A month ago I was playing a pairs tournament in Bulgaria. As always, after the evening session, we were sitting at the bar with friends discussing the deals, perhaps the best part of the tournament.
As you can imagine, everybody wanted to share their best deals, how well they played a hand, what kind of endplay or squeeze they succeed to execute and so on..
Suddenly, I had realized that all stories were from the declarer point of view. 
Almost nobody tried to describe a good hand in defense.   Well, I found this unfair!
And here we are...  In these 2 sessions I would like to show you the beauty of defense.
The deals are selected from real life and have been played by some of best players in the world ever!
I will share with you who were the star players who had played the hands. And you will be able to try to find their defense.
Let's go. GOOD LUCK |
